quran[564]{c,v,t}:
  78,1,Of what do they ask each other
  78,2,Of the mighty information
  78,3,whereon they do dispute
  78,4,"nay, they shall know too well"
  78,5,"Again, nay, they shall know too well"
  78,6,Have we not set the earth as a couch
  78,7,and the mountains as stakes
  78,8,and created you in pairs
  78,9,and made your sleep for rest
  78,10,and made the night a garment
  78,11,and made the day for livelihood
  78,12,and built above you seven solid (heavens)
  78,13,and set a burning lamp
  78,14,"and, sent down from the rain-expressing clouds water pouring forth"
  78,15,to bring out thereby the grain and herb
  78,16,and gardens thickly planted
  78,17,"Verily, the day of decision is an appointed time"
  78,18,"and the day when the trumpet shall be blown, and ye shall come in troops"
  78,19,"and the heavens shall be opened, and shall be all doors"
  78,20,"and the mountains shall be moved, and shall be like a mirage"
  78,21,"Verily, hell is an ambuscade"
  78,22,a reward for the outrageous
  78,23,to tarry therein for ages
  78,24,They shall not taste therein cool nor drink
  78,25,but only boiling water and pus
  78,26,a fit reward
  78,27,"Verily, they did not hope for the account"
  78,28,but they ever said our signs were lies
  78,29,Everything have we remembered in a book
  78,30,"Then taste, for we will only increase your torment"
  78,31,"Verily, for the pious is a blissful place"
  78,32,gardens and vineyards
  78,33,and girls with swelling breasts of the same age as themselves
  78,34,and a brimming cup
  78,35,they shall hear therein no folly and no lie
  78,36,"a reward from thy Lord, a sufficient gift"
  78,37,"The Lord of the heavens and the earth, and what is between them both,- the Merciful,- they cannot obtain audience of Him"
  78,38,"The day when the Spirit and the angels shall stand in ranks, they shall not speak save to whom the Merciful permits, and who speaks aright"
  78,39,That is the true day; and whoso pleases let him take to a resort unto his Lord
  78,40,"Verily, we have warned you of a torment that is nigh: on a day when man shall see what his two hands have sent forward; and the misbeliever shall say, 'Would that I were dust"
  79,1,By those who tear out violently
  79,2,And by those who gaily release
  79,3,And by those who float through the air
  79,4,And the preceders who precede
  79,5,And those who manage the affair
  79,6,On the day when the quaking quakes
  79,7,which the following one shall succeed
  79,8,Hearts on that day shall tremble
  79,9,eyes thereon be humbled
  79,10,"They say, 'Shall we be sent back to our old course"
  79,11,What! when we are rotten bones
  79,12,"they say, 'That then were a losing return"
  79,13,But it will only be one scare
  79,14,and lo! they will be on the surface
  79,15,Has the story of Moses come to you
  79,16,when his Lord addressed him in the holy valley of Tuva
  79,17,"Go unto Pharaoh, verily, he is outrageous"
  79,18,"and say, \"Hast thou a wish to purify thyself"
  79,19,"and that I may guide thee to thy Lord, and thou mayest fear"
  79,20,So he showed him the greatest signs
  79,21,but he called him a liar and rebelled
  79,22,Then he retreated hastily
  79,23,"and gathered, and proclaimed"
  79,24,"and said, 'I am your Lord most High"
  79,25,but God seized him with the punishment of the future life and of the former
  79,26,"Verily, in that is a lesson to him who fears"
  79,27,Are ye harder to create or the heaven that He has built
  79,28,He raised its height and fashioned it
  79,29,"and made its night to cover it, and brought forth its noonday light"
  79,30,and the earth after that He did stretch out
  79,31,He brings forth from it its water and its pasture
  79,32,And the mountains He did firmly set
  79,33,a provision for you and for your cattle
  79,34,And when the great predominant calamity shall come
  79,35,on the day when man shall remember what he strove after
  79,36,and hell shall be brought out for him who sees
  79,37,And as for him who was outrageous
  79,38,and preferred the life of this world
  79,39,"verily, hell is the resort"
  79,40,"But as for him who feared the station of his Lord, and prohibited his soul from lust"
  79,41,"verily, Paradise is the resort"
  79,42,"They shall ask thee about the Hour, for when it is set"
  79,43,Whereby canst thou mention it
  79,44,Unto thy Lord its period belongs
  79,45,Thou art only a warner to him who fears it
  79,46,"On the day they see it, it will be as though they had only tarried an evening or the noon thereof"
  80,1,He frowned and turned his back
  80,2,for that there came to him a blind man
  80,3,But what should make thee know whether haply he may be purified
  80,4,or may be mindful and the reminder profit him
  80,5,But as for him who is wealthy
  80,6,thou dost attend to him
  80,7,and thou dost not care that he is not purified
  80,8,but as for him who comes to thee earnestly
  80,9,fearing the while
  80,10,from him thou art diverted
  80,11,"Nay! verily, it is a memorial"
  80,12,and whoso pleases will remember it
  80,13,In honoured pages
  80,14,"exalted, purified"
  80,15,in the hands of
  80,16,"noble, righteous scribes"
  80,17,May man be killed! how ungrateful he is
  80,18,Of what did He create him
  80,19,Of a clot. He created him and fated him
  80,20,then the path He did make easy for him
  80,21,"then He killed him, and laid him in the tomb"
  80,22,then when He pleases will He raise him up again
  80,23,"Nay, he has not fulfilled his bidding"
  80,24,But let man look unto his foods
  80,25,"Verily, we have poured the water out in torrents"
  80,26,then we have cleft the earth asunder
  80,27,and made to grow therefrom the grain
  80,28,"and the grape, and the hay"
  80,29,"and the olive, and the palm"
  80,30,and gardens closely planted
  80,31,"and fruits, and grass"
  80,32,a provision for you and for your cattle
  80,33,But when the stunning noise shall come
  80,34,on the day when man shall flee from his brother
  80,35,and his mother and his father
  80,36,and his spouse and his sons
  80,37,Every man among them on that day shall have a business to employ him
  80,38,Faces on that day shall be bright
  80,39,"laughing, joyous"
  80,40,and faces shall have dust upon them
  80,41,darkness shall cover them
  80,42,those are the wicked misbelievers
  81,1,When the sun is folded up
  81,2,And when the stars do fall
  81,3,And when the mountains are moved
  81,4,And when the she-camels ten months gone with young shall be neglected
  81,5,And when the beasts shall be crowded together
  81,6,And when the seas shall surge up
  81,7,And when souls shall be paired with bodies
  81,8,And when the child who was buried alive shall be asked
  81,9,for what sin she was slain
  81,10,And when the pages shall be spread out
  81,11,And when the heaven shall be flayed
  81,12,And when hell shall be set ablaze
  81,13,And when Paradise shall be brought nigh
  81,14,The soul shall know what it has produced
  81,15,I need not swear by the stars that slink back
  81,16,"moving swiftly, slinking into their dens"
  81,17,Nor by the night when darkness draws on
  81,18,Nor by the morn when it first breathes up
  81,19,"Verily, it is the speech of a noble apostle"
  81,20,"mighty, standing sure with the Lord of the throne"
  81,21,obeyed and trusty too
  81,22,Your comrade is not mad
  81,23,he saw him on the plain horizon
  81,24,nor does he grudge to communicate the unseen
  81,25,Nor is it the speech of a pelted devil
  81,26,Then whither do ye go
  81,27,It is but a reminder to the worlds
  81,28,to whomsoever of you pleases to go straight
  81,29,"but ye will not please, except God, the Lord of the world, should please"
  82,1,When the heaven is cleft asunder
  82,2,And when the stars are scattered
  82,3,And when the seas gush together
  82,4,And when the tombs are turned upside down
  82,5,The soul shall know what it has sent on or kept back
  82,6,O man! what has seduced thee concerning thy generous Lord
  82,7,"who created thee, and fashioned thee, and gave thee symmetry"
  82,8,and in what form He pleased composed thee
  82,9,"Nay, but ye call the judgment a lie"
  82,10,but over you are guardians set
  82,11,"noble, writing down"
  82,12,they know what ye do
  82,13,"Verily, the righteous are in pleasure"
  82,14,"and, verily, the wicked are in hell"
  82,15,they shall broil therein upon the judgment day
  82,16,nor shall they be absent therefrom
  82,17,And what shall make thee know what is the judgment day
  82,18,"Again, what shall make thee know what is the judgment day"
  82,19,a day when no soul shall control aught for another; and the bidding on that day belongs to God
  83,1,Woe to those who give short weight
  83,2,who when they measure against others take full measure
  83,3,"but when they measure to them or weigh to them, diminish"
  83,4,Do not these think that they shall be raised again
  83,5,at the mighty day
  83,6,the day when men shall stand before the Lord of the worlds
  83,7,"Nay, verily, the book of the wicked is in Siggin"
  83,8,and what shall make thee know what Siggin is
  83,9,a book inscribed
  83,10,Woe on that day for those who say it is a lie
  83,11,Who call the judgment day a lie
  83,12,but none shall call it a lie except every sinful transgressor
  83,13,"who, when our signs are read to him, says, Old folks tales"
  83,14,"Nay, but that which they have gained has settled upon their hearts"
  83,15,"Nay, verily, from their Lord on that day are they veiled"
  83,16,"and then, verily, they shall broil in hell"
  83,17,"then it shall be said, 'This is what ye once did call a lie"
  83,18,"Nay, verily, the book of the righteous is in Illiyun"
  83,19,and what shall make thee know what Illiyun is
  83,20,book inscribed
  83,21,those nigh to God shall witness it
  83,22,"Verily, the righteous shall be in pleasure"
  83,23,upon couches shall they gaze
  83,24,thou mayest recognise in their faces the brightness of pleasure
  83,25,they shall be given to drink wine that is sealed
  83,26,whose seal is musk; for that then let the aspirants aspire
  83,27,and it shall be tempered with Tasnim
  83,28,a spring from which those nigh to God shall drink
  83,29,"Verily, those who sin do laugh at those who believe"
  83,30,and when they pass by they wink at one another
  83,31,and when they return to their family they return ridiculing them
  83,32,"and when they see them they say, Verily, these do go astray"
  83,33,but they are not sent as guardians over them
  83,34,But today those who believe shall at the misbelievers laugh
  83,35,Upon couches shall they gaze
  83,36,are the misbelievers rewarded for what they have done
  84,1,When the heaven is rent asunder
  84,2,"and gives ear unto its Lord, and is dutiful"
  84,3,And when the earth is stretched out
  84,4,"and casts forth what is in it, and is empty"
  84,5,"and gives ear unto its Lord, and is dutiful"
  84,6,"O man! verily, thou are toiling after thy Lord, toiling; wherefore shalt thou meet Him"
  84,7,And as for him who is given his book in his right hand
  84,8,he shall be reckoned with by an easy reckoning
  84,9,and he shall go back to his family joyfully
  84,10,But as for him who is given his book behind his back
  84,11,he shall call out for destruction
  84,12,but he shall broil in a blaze
  84,13,"Verily, he was amongst his family joyful"
  84,14,"Verily, he thought that he should never return to God"
  84,15,"Yea, verily, his Lord on him did look"
  84,16,I need not swear by the evening glow
  84,17,"Or by the night, and what it drives together"
  84,18,Or by the moon when it is at its full
  84,19,Ye shall be surely transferred from state to state
  84,20,What ails them that they do not believe
  84,21,"and, when the Koran is read to them, do not adore"
  84,22,"Nay, those who misbelieve do say it is a lie"
  84,23,but God knows best the (malice) that they hide
  84,24,So give them the glad tidings of grievous woe
  84,25,"save those who believe and act aright, for them is hire that is not grudged"
  85,1,By the heaven with its zodiacal signs
  85,2,And the promised day
  85,3,And the witness and the witnessed
  85,4,The fellows of the pit were slain
  85,5,And the fire with its kindling
  85,6,When they sat over it
  85,7,And witnessed the while what they were doing with those who believed
  85,8,"And they took not vengeance on them save for their belief in God, The mighty, the praiseworthy"
  85,9,Whose is the kingdoms of the heavens and the earth; For God is witness over all
  85,10,"Verily, those who make trial of the believers, men and women, and then do not repent, for them is the torment of hell, and for them is the torment of the burning"
  85,11,"Verily, those who believe and act aright, for them are gardens beneath which rivers flow,- that is the great bliss"
  85,12,"Verily, the violence of thy Lord is keen"
  85,13,"Verily, He produces and returns"
  85,14,"and He is the forgiving, the loving"
  85,15,the Lord of the glorious throne
  85,16,the doer of what He will
  85,17,Has there come to thee the story of the hosts
  85,18,of Pharaoh and Thamud
  85,19,"Nay, those who misbelieve do say it is a lie"
  85,20,but God is behind them - encompassing
  85,21,"Nay, it is a glorious Koran"
  85,22,in a preserved tablet
  86,1,By the heaven and by the night star
  86,2,And what shall make thee know what the night star is
  86,3,The star of piercing brightness
  86,4,"Verily, every soul has a guardian over it"
  86,5,Then let man look from what he is created
  86,6,he is created from water poured forth
  86,7,that comes out from between the loins and the breast bones
  86,8,"Verily, He is able to send him back again"
  86,9,on the day when the secrets shall be tried
  86,10,and he shall have no strength nor helper
  86,11,By the heaven that sends back the rain
  86,12,And the earth with its sprouting
  86,13,"Verily, it is indeed a distinguishing speech"
  86,14,and it is no frivolity
  86,15,"Verily, they do plot a plot"
  86,16,But I plot my plot too
  86,17,let the misbelievers bide; do thou then let them bide awhile
  87,1,Celebrated the name of thy Lord most High
  87,2,who created and fashioned
  87,3,and who decreed and guided
  87,4,and who brings forth the pasture
  87,5,and then makes it dusky stubble
  87,6,"We will make thee recite, and thou shalt not forget"
  87,7,"save what God pleases. Verily, He knows the open and what is concealed"
  87,8,and we will send thee easily to ease
  87,9,"wherefore remind, for, verily, the reminder is useful"
  87,10,But he who fears will be mindful
  87,11,but the wretch will avoid it
  87,12,he who will broil on the great fire
  87,13,and then therein shall neither die nor live
  87,14,Prosperous is he who purifies himself
  87,15,and remembers the name of his Lord and prays
  87,16,Nay! but ye prefer the life of this world
  87,17,while the hereafter is better and more lasting
  87,18,"Verily, this was in the books of yore"
  87,19,the books of Abraham and Moses
  88,1,Has there come to thee the story of the overwhelming
  88,2,Faces on that day shall be humble
  88,3,"labouring, toiling"
  88,4,shall broil upon a burning fire
  88,5,shall be given to drink from a boiling spring
  88,6,no food shall they have save from the foul thorn
  88,7,which shall not fatten nor avail against hunger
  88,8,Faces on that day shall be comfortable
  88,9,content with their past endeavours
  88,10,in a lofty garden
  88,11,wherein they shall hear no foolish word
  88,12,wherein is a flowing fountain
  88,13,wherein are couches raised on high
  88,14,and goblets set down
  88,15,and cushions arranged
  88,16,and carpets spread
  88,17,Do they not look then at the camel how she is created
  88,18,And at the heaven how it is reared
  88,19,And at the mountains how they are set up
  88,20,And at the earth how it is spread out
  88,21,"But remind: thou art only one to remind"
  88,22,thou art not in authority over them
  88,23,except such as turns his back and misbelieves
  88,24,for him will God torment with the greatest torment
  88,25,"Verily, unto us is their return"
  88,26,"and, verily, for us is their account"
  89,1,By the dawn
  89,2,and ten nights
  89,3,And the single and the double
  89,4,And the night when it travels on
  89,5,Is there in that an oath for a man of sense
  89,6,Hast thou not seen how thy Lord did with Ad
  89,7,with Iram of the columns
  89,8,the like of which has not been created in the land
  89,9,And Thamud when they hewed the stones in the valley
  89,10,And Pharaoh of the stakes
  89,11,Who were outrageous in the land
  89,12,and did multiply wickedness therein
  89,13,and thy Lord poured out upon them the scourge of torment
  89,14,"Verily, thy Lord is on a watch tower"
  89,15,"and as for man, whenever his Lord tries him and honours him and grants him favour, then he says, My Lord has honoured me"
  89,16,"but whenever he tries him and doles out to him his subsistence, then he says, My Lord despises me"
  89,17,"Nay, but ye do not honour the orphan"
  89,18,nor do ye urge each other to feed the poor
  89,19,and ye devour the inheritance (of the weak) with a general devouring
  89,20,and ye love wealth with a complete love
  89,21,"Nay, when the earth is crushed to pieces"
  89,22,"and thy Lord comes with the angels, rank on rank"
  89,23,"and hell is brought on that day,- on that day shall man be reminded! but how shall he have a reminder"
  89,24,"He will say, 'Would that I had sent something forward for my life"
  89,25,But on that day no one shall be tormented with a torment like his
  89,26,and none shall be bound with bonds like his
  89,27,O thou comforted soul
  89,28,"return unto thy Lord, well pleased and well pleased with"
  89,29,And enter amongst my servants
  89,30,and enter my Paradise
  90,1,I need not swear by the Lord of this land
  90,2,and though a dweller in this land
  90,3,Nor by the begetter and what he begets
  90,4,We have surely created man in trouble
  90,5,Does he think that none can do aught against him
  90,6,"He says, I have wasted wealth in plenty"
  90,7,does he think that no one sees him
  90,8,Have we not made for him two eyes
  90,9,"and a tongue, and two lips"
  90,10,and guided him in the two highways
  90,11,but he will not attempt the steep
  90,12,And what shall make thee know what the steep is
  90,13,It is freeing captives
  90,14,or feeding on the day of famine
  90,15,an orphan who is akin
  90,16,or a poor man who lies in the dust
  90,17,"and again (it is) to be of these who believe and encourage each other to patience, and encourage each other to mercy"
  90,18,these are the fellows of the right
  90,19,"But those who disbelieve in our signs, they are the fellows of the left"
  90,20,for them is fire that closes in
  91,1,By the sun and its noonday brightness
  91,2,And the moon when it follows him
  91,3,And the day when it displays him
  91,4,And the night when it covers him
  91,5,And the heaven and what built it
  91,6,And the earth and what spread it
  91,7,"And the soul and what fashioned it, and taught it"
  91,8,its sin and its piety
  91,9,Prosperous is he who purifies it
  91,10,And disappointed is he who corrupts it
  91,11,Thamud called the apostle a liar in their outrage
  91,12,when their wretch rose up
  91,13,"and the apostle of God said to them, God's she-camel! so give her to drink"
  91,14,"But they called him a liar, and they ham-strung her; but their Lord destroyed them in their sins, and served them all alike"
  91,15,and He fears not the result thereof
  92,1,By the night when it veils
  92,2,And the day when it is displayed
  92,3,And by what created male and female
  92,4,"Verily, your efforts are diverse"
  92,5,But as for him who gives alms and fears God
  92,6,And believes in the best
  92,7,We will send him easily to ease
  92,8,"But as for him who is niggardly, And longs for wealth"
  92,9,And calls the good a lie
  92,10,We will send him easily to difficulty
  92,11,And his wealth shall not avail him When he falls down (into hell)
  92,12,"Verily, it is for us to guide"
  92,13,"And, verily, ours are the hereafter and the former life"
  92,14,And I have warned you of a fire that flames
  92,15,"None shall broil thereon, but the most wretched"
  92,16,who says it is a lie and turns his back
  92,17,But the pious shall be kept away from it
  92,18,he who gives his wealth in alms
  92,19,and who gives no favour to any one for the sake of reward
  92,20,but only craving the face of his Lord most High
  92,21,in the end he shall be well pleased
  93,1,By the forenoon
  93,2,And the night when it darkens
  93,3,"Thy Lord has not forsaken thee, nor hated thee"
  93,4,and surely the hereafter is better for thee than the former
  93,5,"and in the end thy Lord will give thee, and thou shalt be well pleased"
  93,6,"Did He not find thee an orphan, and give the shelter"
  93,7,"and find thee erring, and guide thee"
  93,8,"and find thee poor with a family, and nourish thee"
  93,9,But as for the orphan oppress him not
  93,10,and as for the beggar drive him not away
  93,11,and as for the favour of thy Lord discourse thereof
  94,1,Have we not expanded for thee thy breast
  94,2,and set down from thee thy load
  94,3,which galled thy back
  94,4,and exalted for thee thy renown
  94,5,"Verily, with difficulty is ease"
  94,6,"verily, with difficulty is ease"
  94,7,And when thou art at leisure then toil
  94,8,and for thy Lord do thou yearn
  95,1,By the fig! And by the olive
  95,2,And by Mount Sinai
  95,3,And by this safe land
  95,4,We have indeed created man in the best of symmetry
  95,5,Then we will send him back the lowest of the low
  95,6,save those who believe and act aright; for theirs is a hire that is not grudged
  95,7,But what shall make thee call the judgment after this a lie
  95,8,Is not God a most just of judges
  96,1,"READ, in the name of thy Lord"
  96,2,Who created man from congealed blood
  96,3,"Read, for thy Lord is most generous"
  96,4,Who taught the pen
  96,5,Taught man what he did not know
  96,6,"Nay, verily, man is indeed outrageous"
  96,7,at seeing himself get rich
  96,8,"Verily, unto thy Lord is the return"
  96,9,Hast thou considered him who forbids
  96,10,a servant when he prays
  96,11,Hast thou considered if he were in guidance
  96,12,or bade piety
  96,13,"Hast thou considered if he said it was a lie, and turned his back"
  96,14,Did he not know that God can see
  96,15,"Nay, surely, if he do not desist we will drag him by the forelock"
  96,16,the lying sinful forelock
  96,17,So let him call his counsel
  96,18,we will call the guards of hell
  96,19,"Nay, obey him not, but adore and draw nigh"
  97,1,"Verily, we sent it down on the Night of Power"
  97,2,And what shall make thee know what the Night of Power is
  97,3,the Night of Power is better than a thousand months
  97,4,"The angels and the Spirit descend therein, by the permission of their Lord with every bidding"
  97,5,Peace it is until rising of the dawn
  98,1,Those of the people of the Book and the idolaters who misbelieve did not fall off until there came to them the manifest sign
  98,2,An apostle from God reading pure pages
  98,3,wherein are right scriptures
  98,4,Nor did those who were given the Book divide into sects until after there came to them the manifest sign
  98,5,"But they were not bidden aught but to worship God, being sincere in religion unto Him as Hanifs, and to be steadfast in prayer, and to give alms: for that is the standard religion"
  98,6,"Verily, those who disbelieve amongst the people of the Book and the idolaters shall be in the fire of hell, to dwell therein for aye; they are wretched creatures"
  98,7,"Verily, those who believe and act aright, they are the best of creatures"
  98,8,"their reward with their Lord is gardens of Eden, beneath which rivers flow, to dwell therein for aye; God shall be well pleased with them, and they with Him! that is for him who fears his Lord"
  99,1,When the earth shall quake with its quaking
  99,2,And the earth shall bring forth her burdens
  99,3,"and man shall say, What ails her"
  99,4,On that day she shall tell her tidings
  99,5,because thy Lord inspires her
  99,6,On the day when men shall come up in separate bands to show their works
  99,7,and he who does the weight of an atom of good shall see it
  99,8,and he who does the weight of an atom of evil shall see it
  100,1,By the snorting chargers
  100,2,And those who strike fire with their hoofs
  100,3,And those who make incursions in the morning
  100,4,And raise up dust therein
  100,5,And cleave through a host therein
  100,6,"Verily, man is to his Lord ungrateful"
  100,7,"and, verily, he is a witness of that"
  100,8,"Verily, he is keen in his love of good"
  100,9,Does he not know when the tombs are exposed
  100,10,and what is in the breasts is brought to light
  100,11,"Verily, thy Lord upon that day indeed is well aware"
  101,1,The smiting
  101,2,What is the smiting
  101,3,And what shall make thee know what the smiting is
  101,4,The day when men shall be like scattered moths
  101,5,and the mountains shall be like flocks of carded wool
  101,6,And as for him whose balance is heavy
  101,7,he shall be in a well-pleasing life
  101,8,But as for him whose balance is light
  101,9,his dwelling shall be the pit of hell
  101,10,And who shall make thee know what it is
  101,11,a burning fire
  102,1,The contention about numbers deludes you
  102,2,till ye visit the tombs
  102,3,Not so! In the end ye shall know
  102,4,And again not so! In the end ye shall know
  102,5,Not so! Did ye but know with certain knowledge
  102,6,Ye shall surely see hell
  102,7,And again ye shall surely see it with an eye of certainty
  102,8,Then ye shall surely be asked about pleasure
  103,1,By the afternoon
  103,2,"verily, man is in loss"
  103,3,"save those who believe and do right, and bid each other be true, and bid each other be patient"
  104,1,Woe to every slanderous backbiter
  104,2,who collects wealth and counts it
  104,3,He thinks that his wealth can immortalize him
  104,4,Not so! he shall be hurled into ElHutamah
  104,5,And what shall make thee understand what ElHutamah is
  104,6,the fire of God kindled
  104,7,which rises above the hearts
  104,8,"Verily, it is an archway over them"
  104,9,on long-drawn columns
  105,1,Hast thou not seen what thy Lord did with the fellows of the elephant
  105,2,Did He not make their stratagem lead them astray
  105,3,and send down on them birds in flocks
  105,4,to throw down on them stones of baked clay
  105,5,and make them like blades of herbage eaten down
  106,1,For the uniting of the Qurais
  106,2,uniting them for the caravan of winter and summer
  106,3,So let them serve the Lord of this house
  106,4,who feeds them against hunger and makes them safe against fear
  107,1,Hast thou considered him who calls the judgment a lie
  107,2,He it is who pushes the orphan away
  107,3,and urges not (others) to feed the poor
  107,4,But woe to those who pray
  107,5,and who are careless in their prayers
  107,6,Who pretend
  107,7,and withhold necessaries
  108,1,"Verily, we have given thee El Kauthar"
  108,2,So pray to thy Lord and slaughter (victims)
  108,3,"Verily, he who hates thee shall be childless"
  109,1,"Say, O ye misbelievers"
  109,2,I do not serve what ye serve
  109,3,nor will ye serve what I serve
  109,4,nor will I serve what ye serve
  109,5,nor will ye serve what I serve
  109,6,"ye have your religion, and I have my religion"
  110,1,When there comes God's help and victory
  110,2,And thou shalt see men enter into God's religion by troops
  110,3,"Then celebrate the praises of thy Lord, and ask forgiveness of Him, verily, He is relentant"
  111,1,"Abu Lahebs two hands shall perish, and he shall perish"
  111,2,"His wealth shall not avail him, nor what he has earned"
  111,3,He shall broil in a fire that flames
  111,4,and his wife carrying faggots
  111,5,on her neck a cord of palm fibres
  112,1,"Say, He is God alone"
  112,2,God the Eternal
  112,3,He begets not and is not begotten
  112,4,Nor is there like unto Him any one
  113,1,"Say, I seek refuge in the Lord of the daybreak"
  113,2,from the evil of what He has created
  113,3,and from the evil of the night when it cometh on
  113,4,and from the evil of the blowers upon knots
  113,5,and from the evil of the envious when he envies
  114,1,"Say, I seek refuge in the Lord of men"
  114,2,the King of men
  114,3,the God of men
  114,4,"from the evil of the whisperer, who slinks off"
  114,5,who whispers into the hearts of men
  114,6,from ginns and men